	(text "There's a transistor on the display board."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 593.09 89.408 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.8 0.8)
			)
		)
		(uuid "fb3a6763-6f52-4876-a6c3-a6a58e7272d9")
	)
	(text_box "ESP32-S3 strapping pins:\n* GPIO0 weak pull-up, default 1 (boot mode selection)\n* GPIO3 floating (for JTAG control, unused if not burning efuses)\n* GPIO45 weak pull-down, default 0 (VDD_SPI voltage control, should be left default 0)\n* GPIO46 weak pull-down, default 0 (also boot mode selection, we always want it 0 at startup)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 119.38 39.37 0)
		(size 49.53 13.97)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "07302b45-17f5-40a9-b307-7dc77713dc57")
	)
	(text_box "I2C addresses used:\n\n0011000 - accelerometer\n0101100 - USB Hub\n1110xxx - GPIO expanders\n0011xxx - I2C multiplexers\n1010000 - other USB Hub (in the expander cable)\n\nI2C topology:\n\nI2C1 -> I2C multiplexer @ 0011111 -> servos 1, 2, 3\n                                  -> GPIO expander @ 1110000\n                                  -> USB Hub @ 0101100\n\nI2C2 -> I2C multiplexer @ 0011111 -> servos 4, 5, 6\n                                  -> GPIO expander @ 1110000\n                                  -> accelerometer @ 0011000"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 13.97 113.1345 0)
		(size 69.85 38.117)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "DejaVu Sans Mono")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1293e6ea-ea78-4963-8782-4b4824e0ae38")
	)
	(text_box "This circuit board has WiFi connectivity and controls up to 24 Hex Mini Motor Drives via a USB hub network.\n* ESP32-S3 as main control processor with WiFi and Bluetooth.\n* CAN bus for external motors, onwards connection.\n* Touch Screen for setup and manual controls.\n* USB input for programming/command and control.\n* 6x USB outputs; together with 4x USB cable expanders controls up to 24 hex mini motor drives."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12.7 21.59 0)
		(size 132.08 11.5635)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1 1)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1f2cd93c-8b7e-4e68-aa3b-015869c6a291")
	)
	(text_box "Note: probes 1, 2 and 4 are reversed! For easier wiring."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 342.9 300.5724 0)
		(size 27.94 8.0376)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "4db439eb-41e1-4849-930d-23be57740be3")
	)
	(text_box "CAN Slope control. This 10k resistor slightly slows down the level transition."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 365.76 162.2118 0)
		(size 24.13 4.1582)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.7 0.7)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "5b68271f-a804-4755-ab36-ddf68605934a")
	)
	(text_box "Servo connectors with USB-C and power via FPC\n\nEach hierarchical component represents a pair of USB-C and FPC connectors\nfor a downstream device.\n\nThe NRST and BOOT0 wires can be connected either way and also double\nas I2C connectors for further multiplexing downstream devices. We\nneed to connect them to the GPIO and I2C multiplexers. They will have\nthe following options:\n	1. The STM32 servo drivers will have a pull-up on NRST and pull-down on BOOT0.\n	We will use the GPIO multiplexer to first read the values to determine the plug\n	orientation then we can toggle the lines to enter the bootloader mode to upload\n	code without the device ever being programmed.\n	2. If both lines are pulled up then we have connected a downstream multiplexer.\n	Test out which way the connection works by attempting an I2C transaction; note\n	send some blank data in order to reset the data lines if we have guessed wrong.\n	3. If both lines are pulled down, then it's probably not our device."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 15.24 228.7676 0)
		(size 107.95 36.6624)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "64ee41d2-56b2-475c-bcd8-6734f041c47e")
	)
	(text_box "Note: probes 6, 8 are reversed! For easier wiring."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 342.9 356.87 0)
		(size 27.94 8.0376)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
